org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser

Class KeyedDiffuserRepository

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser.KeyedDiffuserRepository

  • public class KeyedDiffuserRepository
extends java.lang.Object
    Repository that holds diffusers. The global repository uses the KeyedDiffuserRepository.SharedRegistry's Class as a key and can be accessed via getInstance(). Local or private repositories can be created and accessed through the getInstance(Object) with a key. Each repository holds a set of diffusers and their associated keys. The default diffuser can be accessed through getDiffuser() method and set through the setDiffuser(Diffuser) method. Other diffusers may be added and accessed through the putDiffuser(String, Diffuser) and getDiffuser(String) methods where the first argument is the key to that diffuser.
    Author:
    Robert Philipp
